(
<figureCitation id="135DFE86FF9AFF82FBDFFA9DB9A56E8B" box="[1101,1165,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[132,143,1939,1957]" captionTargetBox="[141,1443,214,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[132,1455,201,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 3. — Begonia ambodiforahensis Scherber. &amp; Duruiss., sp. nov.: A, habit; B, leaf, adaxial side; C, male flower, front view; D, male flower, side view; E, androecium; F, female flower, face view; G, female flower, side view; H, gynoecium; I, styles and stigmas; J, Ovary cross-section. A, from a picture in the type locality, not collected; B-J, from a cultivated plant (no. 150333), Lyon Botanical Garden (Drawing: Vanessa Damianthe). Scale bars: A, 1cm; B, 5 mm; C, D, F, G, 2 mm; E, H-J, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4602165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4602165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
